@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
  IDer was written in response to my need for a program that would--when
  provided with arguments--examine a file, and determine an appropriate tool
  to view the file.

  I downloaded one such program from Aminet, but found it severely lacking;
  massively large and slow to use and configure.  I was therefore forced to
  write my own.

  When I started writing IDer, I decided that it should be easy to use, yet
  very powerful.  And I feel I have accomplished this with the first release
  of IDer.

  IDer can recognise an unlimited number of filetypes, and uses a range of
  methods to identify different files.  In addition, IDer can also recognise
  files that have been crunched.
@endnode

